The paper focuses on 3D shape recognition using deep learning models, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed Point-View Relation Network (PVRNet) involves the fusion of point cloud and multi-view data, which requires a good understanding of the relationship between the two modalities. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which may be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed model on a dataset, which may be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
